<abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Letter Book Copy: letters copied into a bound letter-book ]">LB</abbr>, <span class="ref-rep" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ U.S. Library of Congress, George Washington Papers, Washington, D.C. ]">DLC:GW</span>; 
copy, <span class="ref-rep" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ U.S. National Archives and Records Administration, Papers of the Continental Congress, Washington, D.C. ]">DNA:PCC</span>, item 169; 
copy, <span class="ref-rep" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Morristown National Historical Park, Morristown, N.J. [[former abbreviation: NjMoHP]] ]">NjMoHP</span>; 
<abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Handwritten copies in one of the bound volumes used by the team of clerks on GW's headquarters staff who worked from 1781-83 under the direction of Lt. Col. Richard Varick to record correspondence, orders, instructions, and related items from GWs Revolutionary War papers ]">Varick transcript</abbr>, <span class="ref-rep" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ U.S. Library of Congress, George Washington Papers, Washington, D.C. ]">DLC:GW</span>.
 Congress read this letter on 27 Jan. (<span class="ref-st" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Worthington Chauncey Ford et al., eds. &lt;i&gt;Journals of the Continental Congress, 1774-1789&lt;/i&gt;. 34 vols. Washington, D.C., 190437. ]"><span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">JCC</span></span>, 4:94).</p>

</div>
<div id="fn" class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-03-03-02-0100-fn-0001-ptr" id="GEWN-03-03-02-0100-fn-0001">1</a>

   <p>See <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-03-03-02-0056" class="document">Schuyler to GW, 13 Jan</a>., and <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-03-03-02-0092" class="document">Council of War, 18 Jan. 1776</a>.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-03-03-02-0100-fn-0002-ptr" id="GEWN-03-03-02-0100-fn-0002">2</a>

   <p>See Schuyler to Hancock, 13 Jan. 1776, quoted in <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-03-03-02-0056" class="document">Schuyler to GW, that date, n.2</a>.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-03-03-02-0100-fn-0003-ptr" id="GEWN-03-03-02-0100-fn-0003">3</a>

   <p>Congress authorized nine battalions for the defense of Canada on 8 Jan. (<span class="ref-st" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Worthington Chauncey Ford et al., eds. &lt;i&gt;Journals of the Continental Congress, 1774-1789&lt;/i&gt;. 34 vols. Washington, D.C., 190437. ]"><span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">JCC</span></span>, 4:3940).</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-03-03-02-0100-fn-0004-ptr" id="GEWN-03-03-02-0100-fn-0004">4</a>

   <p>For Congresss approval of GWs action in this matter, see <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-03-03-02-0153" class="document">Hancock to GW, 29 Jan. 1776</a>.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-03-03-02-0100-fn-0005-ptr" id="GEWN-03-03-02-0100-fn-0005">5</a>

   <p>See <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-03-03-02-0099" class="document">Circular to the Governments of Massachusetts, Connecticut, and New Hampshire, this date</a>, and the resolution of the Massachusetts General Court, 16 Jan., quoted in <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-03-03-02-0055&amp;expandNote=GEWN-03-03-02-0055-fn-0002#GEWN-03-03-02-0055-fn-0002" class="document">GW to the Massachusetts General Court, 13 Jan. 1776, n.2</a>.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-03-03-02-0100-fn-0006-ptr" id="GEWN-03-03-02-0100-fn-0006">6</a>

   <p>In response to GWs circular letter of this date, the General Court resolved this afternoon to comply with his request for a regiment to reinforce the army in Canada and that it be raised in Hampshire and Berkshire counties. The resolution that actually authorized the raising of that regiment was not approved until 21 Jan. (<span class="ref-st" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ &lt;i&gt;A Journal of the Honourable House of Representatives. At a Great and General Court or Assembly for the Colony of the Massachusetts-Bay in New-England&lt;/i&gt;. Boston, 1776. (Microfilm Collection of Early State Records.) ]"><span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">Mass. House of Rep. Journal</span>, Nov. 1775Feb. 1776 sess.</span>, 167, 17476, 17884; <span class="ref-st" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ In &lt;i&gt;Journals, Minutes, and Proceedings, State of Massachusetts Bay, 17751780&lt;/i&gt;. (Microfilm Collection of Early State Records.) ]">Mass. Council Journal, July 1775Feb. 1776 sess.</span>, 470, 47678, 482, 48591; see also the printed copy of the resolution of 21 Jan. in <span class="ref-rep" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ U.S. Library of Congress, George Washington Papers, Washington, D.C. ]">DLC:GW</span>).</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-03-03-02-0100-fn-0007-ptr" id="GEWN-03-03-02-0100-fn-0007">7</a>

   <p>See <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-03-03-02-0097" class="document">Trumbull to GW, 18 Jan. 1776</a>.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-03-03-02-0100-fn-0008-ptr" id="GEWN-03-03-02-0100-fn-0008">8</a>

   <p>For the sending of these commissions, see <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-03-03-02-0153" class="document">Hancock to GW, 29 Jan. 1776</a>.</p>

</div>
